Oldham County Public Library of Texas
June 24 at 10:10 PM Â·

This coming Wednesday, July 1st will be our first day of our summer reading program. We are super excited! It will be here at the library every Wednesday of July from 2:30p.m to 4:00p.m. We will have a read aloud, check-out time, crafts, and refreshments. We will also be doing reading logs with prizes. This first reading program is Independence Day themed, so come wearing your Red, White, and Blue. It will be a blast, so we hope to see everyone ages going into kindergarten (5 years old) to 6th grade there!! Please call the library to let us know if your coming.

Good morning from Vega ISD, we have received 128 replies on our parent survey. I would like to thank you all for taking the time to respond and if you havenâ€™t please do so. The comments that you have made are very appreciated and will be utilized as we move forward.
Just FYI, Nurse Cayla has been stocking up on thermometers and health supplies and we have also stocked up on cleaning and sanitizing supplies. With the building being vacant the last couple of months, it has allowed our janitors to do some deep, deep cleaning on our facility.
I was very pleased with the results of this survey. I know Iâ€™m ready to see the kids and I truly believe their teachers are as well.
Once again thank you and itâ€™s a great day to be a Longhorn,
Jody Johnson

To Parents:

This school year has gone so fast it seems; especially with the COVID-19 situation having taken us to distance learning for our students. Mrs. Atkins, Mrs. Martinez, and I want all our kids to know that we miss seeing them every day for lunch and we look forward to seeing them all again at the start of the new school year.
As you all know, May 21st was scheduled to be the last day of school as we let out for summer vacation. The Cafeteria will be keeping to this schedule; our last day of "To Go" meal service will be May 21st.
As a friendly reminder, students with outstanding meal balances can be be paid online through MySchoolBucks.com. If you don't have an account, one will need to be created. We are also taking payments through the mail; Vega ISD, Attn. Cafeteria, P.O. Box 190 Vega, TX. 79092.
If there is an outstanding balance for 8th grade students, these balances MUST BE PAID IN FULL by May 21st.

Sincerely,

Talia Carter
Food Service Director
Vega ISD EL/JH Cafeteria

post_text:
Well, Iâ€™d like to say good afternoon from Vega ISD but I figure most of you saw Governor Abbottâ€™s press conference. I know I preach being positive but it is hard right now because I was really hoping for us to be able to finish out this year here at school. I knew it was probably not going to happen but I was hoping.
Mike Morath, Commissioner of Education, will be giving us some direction on how to finish up this school year educating our students and also some guidelines for graduation. Mrs. Rosas has already been thinking about Baccalaureate and graduation and she has some great ideas. We are open to any suggestions, contact her if you have ideas. We want to celebrate the great accomplishments that this senior class has had throughout the years at Vega High.
I know we have staff members upset over this decision as am I. We love our kids and we miss each and everyone of them. We will continue to move forward for the next month with our distance learning or until the state gives us other directives.
Have a great evening and remember, Longhorn Pride!

post_text:
Good afternoon from Vega ISD, it was so good to see some of our students this morning and we miss each and everyone one of you. I know we all got choked up at times throughout the whole trip.
Governor Abbott had a news conference this afternoon and has ordered schools to continue distance learning until May 4th. I know this is an inconvenience to everyone (students, teachers and parents) and we all want to get back to school. Hang in there and Iâ€™m talking to everybody. If youâ€™re having issues, communicate with your teachers and principals. We have been at it for four/five days and we will continue to monitor our progress and make adjustments as needed.
Vega ISD will persevere throughout this crisis!!
Itâ€™s a great day to be a Longhorn!!!
text:
Good afternoon from Vega ISD, it was so good to see some of our students this morning and we miss each and everyone one of you. I know we all got choked up at times throughout the whole trip.
Governor Abbott had a news conference this afternoon and has ordered schools to continue distance learning until May 4th. I know this is an inconvenience to everyone (students, teachers and parents) and we all want to get back to school. Hang in there and Iâ€™m talking to everybody. If youâ€™re having issues, communicate with your teachers and principals. We have been at it for four/five days and we will continue to monitor our progress and make adjustments as needed.
Vega ISD will persevere throughout this crisis!!
Itâ€™s a great day to be a Longhorn!!!

post_text:
Good evening, I can imagine there are some people totally stressing out after the first day of distance learning!! Please take a breath, we are all in uncharted waters. This is new for us all(teachers, students and parents) and we will all need to work together to make this work.
One thing that I want to stress, I expect our students to continue to work. It is a proven fact that students regress over the summer, can you imagine how far behind your child would be if we gave up on this year.
Please be patient and if you have questions or concerns contact the teachers and principals. If you have technology issues please contact Mrs. Kirkland.
Once again, this is a day to day, week to week process and we will be monitoring and adjusting as we go.
I pray that this virus passes and we can get back to school and some normalcy. I miss seeing and talking to your kids and I know their teachers feel the same.

post_text:
Good afternoon from Vega ISD, many of you probably heard Gov. Abbottâ€™s address this morning. Vega ISD will be closed from March 23- April 3 for all students.

We have had preliminary plans in place in case we were forced to close. We will be rolling those plans for distance learning out this week. Our campus principals and teachers will be in contact with you as soon as we get it all up and running.

All staff will meet at 9:00 Monday morning.

I am sorry for the inconvenience that this is going to place on all of our families. We were definitely hoping to be able and stay open and try and keep some normalcy in this part of our state but this is a situation that none of us have ever experienced! We will always make decisions for the safety and security of our students, school and community.

Texas FCCLA
March 16 at 4:37 PM Â·

On Friday, March 13, 2020 the Texas FCCLA Board of Directors made the decision to cancel the 2020 State Leadership Conference that was scheduled to take place in Dallas April 2-4, 2020.

It was not an easy decision but one that was made in the interest of the health and safety of our members, advisors, volunteers, staff, and the communities in which we reside.

We know that members and advisors across our great state have been working hard to prepare for the State Leadership Conference and we (the Texas FCCLA State Staff, the Board of Directors, and the State Executive Council) are both so very proud of what each member and chapter has accomplished this school year and upset that you will not be able to fully showcase these efforts at the State Leadership Conference.

Please read the release for additional information.

Vega Longhorn Band
February 10 at 1:01 AM Â·

Yesterday members of the Vega High School Band performed at UIL Solo and Ensemble Contest. All of the kids did outstanding!! I could not be more proud of them. Despite not all of the ensembles making a Division One, all of the judges were VERY complimentary of what the kids in the Vega Band were doing! Below are the results:

Percussion Ensemble (RB Gist, Nathan Lancaster, and Dakota Walker): Division Two
Alto Sax Solo (Chase Terry): Division One
Clarinet Trio (Mary Claire Spinhirne, Kate Tretow, and Brad Turpen): Division One, Advanced to State Solo and Ensemble
Brass Trio (Tyler Wilburn, Joseelin Cruz, and Cameron Tanck): Division One, Advanced to State Solo and Ensemble

Congratulations to all of these kids!!

post_text: We learned so much during our visit to Snack Pak 4 Kids today. They provide snacks for 6,000 Amarillo students and 4,000 additional students in the Texas Panhandle each week! Dyron and Kelly Howell started this program in Amarillo on September 3, 2010. In less than an hour today, we filled over 400 bags. With little effort, our students ensured that at least 400 students will have something to eat this weekend. A tremendous lesson in community service and giving back!
